ENGLISH:

This is a clone of tetris I programmed following the amazing assembly
course by Fabio Ciucci (Randy/Ram-Jam). Sad enough to say, this great
coder has just left te Amiga, and passed where you can imagine... (peesee)
so I haven't been able to test my game and to give it to an experienced
coder. It seems to work on my A4000/030/882 8mb fast both under 3.0
and 1.3 (I couldn't test it on 2.0, sorry, but it must work, because
1.3<2.0<3.0 :) )

I couldn't test it on any Amiga 500, and with 512k of ram.
I might imagine that without 1Mb it won't work. Tell me please.

Select the number of players and the level speed on the first
menu. Use joysticks in both ports. To quit while playing, press
Esc.

-Technical details:

   -Nice features:

      -Programmed entirely in assembler, without the knowledge
       of most OS routines :-»

      -Small intro, as those of partys of ten years ago... (:^¤)

      -Two players versus...

      -A VERY VERY NICE floating sprite

      -Up to 20 speed levels, as on the Gameboy

   -Nasty features:

      -Exaggerated ram usage... I think that 1mb is the minimum

      -The starting zoom routine has not so much been optimized
       so it is slow (chunky to planar real time... 4 times
       sower than real chunky).

